description: Exterior Color: Roman Red/White Coves
Interior: Black
Engine: 283 V8 (NOM)
Transmission: 4 Speed Automatic 700 R4
Miles: 57509 (current odometer reading/not actual)

This is a very nice driver quality 1960 Corvette. It has several upgrades to make it more suited for today's driving conditions. First the brakes have been upgraded to power front disc brakes/drum rear brakes. The cooling system has been upgraded with an electric powered cooling fan, the transmission has been replaced with a 4 speed automatic 700 R4 unit. The generator has been replaced with an alternator, Â The tires are wide whitewall radial tires and the sound system has been changed to a contemporary system.

The paint is 2 stage, base/clear coat and has a good shine,The weather stripping is new including the windshield seal, the black vinyl seat covers are in very nice condition. The chrome and stainless is not show quality but present very well for a driver. There is some minor pitting in some trim and the bumpers' chrome is thin in some spots. The emblems are all present, the hood and trunk emblems do show their age but many enthusiast prefer patina over reproduction pieces.
The 283 V8 is not original to the car but it does run well and has an updated electronic ignition and an Edelbrock carb, chromed valve covers, and a chrome open element air cleaner.Â

There is no denying the style of a 1960 Corvette and this C1 will turn heads. The upgrades make it a nice driver and with only 10,261 Corvettes built in 1960, it is a highly desired car that will bring a lot of attention to the driver.

description: 1029H..1960 Corvette Convertible, two tops, RPO-687, 283-290 hp, (fuelie), 4 speed, numbers matching original motor. Roman Redpaint with Black interior and Black soft top. Very original four owner unmolested and unrestored car with mostly original paint on a NO HIT body. NCRS Second Flight awardin 2012 and recently invited and displayed at the Concours d'Elegance of Texas in April 2016. Also has been presented to a 2013 NCRS Regional for Bowtie Sign-off. Still has its 5 original 5-1/2" big brake wheels, fast steering adapter, heavy duty suspension, AT rear end, transmission, engine, finned brake drums, off road exhaust, and hardtop wrench. Optioned with auxiliary hardtop, T-10 transmission, 4.11 posi for RPO-687, RPO-687 special heavy duty suspension and brakes, Wonderbar radio, off road exhaust, sunvisors, courtesy light, heater, hubcaps, and 6.70x15" blackwall tires. Most all factory correct type components including the spare, jack, jack tools, trunk mat, trunk liner, rebound straps, seat belts, shifter, shielding, air cleaner, generator, distributor, spark plug shields, hoses, hose clamps, grooved rear springs, valve covers, F.I. unit, F.I. fuel filter, guide Y-50 mirror, owners manual, sales brochure, and T-3 headlights. Well-documented car including the owner history since new, old titles back to second owner (1962), service records/maintenance receipts back to 1963, NCRS certificate/judging sheets, Bowtie candidate paperwork, and a large document binder. These original unmolested cars are among the rarest of rare and are rising to the top of the Corvette food chain as unrestored cars are used as guideposts for restorers, shining a light on the way vehicles were originally built. The solid feel of an excellent unrestored car cannot be overstated! This is a 56-year old car that is as pure as they come. The RPO-687 race package was only produced for 119 Corvettes in 1960! Looks, runs, and drives excellent.

Roller Cam, B&M 6:71 Blower, Twin 650 cfm Carbs, MSD Ignition, BTE Turbo 400 Automatic 3 Speed Transmission, PTC Street Fighter Converter, 9 inch Ford Rear, Latter Bar with 3:73 Ratio, Adjustable Coil Over Shocks, Chris Alston Full Frame Kit, Hooker Super Comp Headers with Race Pro Mufflers, Barry Grant Fuel System with all A N Fittings, East Coast Mini-Torque Starter, Griffin 4 Core Alum. Radiator, Fat Man Front End with Tubular A-Arms and Mustang II Rack-N-Pinion Steering, 3 Way Adjustable Front Shocks, Wilwood Disc Brakes, Custom Dash with Auto Meter Gauges, Painless Wiring, Moroso Removable Steering Wheel, RJS Harness, Moroso Hidden Kill Switch, Full Certified Roll Cage, New Paint, New Bumpers, New Lights, New Engine and Trans., New 18 and 20 Inch Billet Specialties Wheels, New Stainless and Chrome, etc. etc... This Corvette Spent Most of it's Life on the Drag Strip in California, where it is still titled as. It was Restored and Turned into a Show Car Street Car 3 years ago. It was brought to the East Coast Last December where it has Won all 4 shows that it has entered. It Won the Peoples Choice at the Spring Corvette Expo in Knoxville TN 2017, 1st at the Southern Rods Show in Bowling Green KY, 2017, 1st at Carl Casper Show in Louisville KY 2017, and 1st at the Nashville Music City Auto Fest in Nashville TN 2017.. It has less than 200 miles put on it since Restored.   It runs Cool and sounds Awesome! If you do not like Attention, Do Not Buy This Car! It has a Awesome Stance, and Drives Even Better. People gather around this Corvette everywhere it goes!

Over $150K Spent on this Beautiful 1960 Corvette.   Asking the FIRM price of $79.5K.  Car located in Hixson, TN.  Inspection encouraged and welcomed by appointment only.  Financing available to qualified candidates.  Shipping; no problem.

description: NSN-DV..1960 Corvette "Sweet Sixteen" Convertible with working powertop, 283-230 hp, powerglide, numbers matching original motor. One family owned car with 57,509 actual miles. Roman Red paint with Black interior and White soft top. Very original NEVER HIT car with one repaint, new interior other than dash pad which is original and nice. Has rust-free chassis and new exhaust. "Sweet Sixteen" was a birthday present for our client's mother on October 13th, 1959. Our client's family has lived with this car for 56 years. Optioned with powerglide, powertop, 3.55 rear, Wonderbar radio, sunvisors, windshield washers, courtesy light, heater, seat belts, hubcaps, and Coker classic wide white tires. Most all factory correct type components including the spare, jack, jack tools, trunk mat, trunk liner, rebound straps, washer system, shifter, shielding, air cleaner, generator, spark plug shields, radiator, warranty book, owners manual, and sales brochure. Documented with acknowledgement of Corvette order, dealer order, dealer invoice, warranty book, Corvette owner patch, Corvette owner club accessories catalog, maintenance records, old title, volumes 3 and 4 of Corvette News, repaint/restore photos and a large 3-binder. Very rare powerglide/powertop (1 of 512) Corvette that is pure, has a great history, and has been loved. First time ever offered for sale!! Looks, runs, and drives excellent
